item.content:encoded: Penthouse Sweets which was founded in 2013, is a boutique dessert studio that specializes in one-of-a-kind custom cakes and dessert bars. Located in Alsip, we proudly service the Chicago and Northwest Indiana area and all its surrounding suburbs. PHS ultimate goal is to be a part of the conversation when it comes to wedding and specialty cakes. Head Pastry Chef Yvonne Ivy-Stephens has grown Penthouse Sweets from a small idea to the region's premier custom dessert vendor.

item.title: Brides by NoNA Fixes All Eyes on You
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Whats the one thing every bride has to get right on her wedding day? If you said the wedding dress, you are right. Even if everything else is awry, the bridal dress is one of the main thing guests will be talking about long after the wedding ceremony. So you better make sure its stunning and not an epic catastrophe. Am I making you nervous? No need to be because one of our vendors on Lamzoaks, has your back. Enter Brides by NoNA a luxury brand of bespoke bridal and formal wear owned by Nigerian-born designer, Nneka C. Alexander.   With a mottoIf you can think it, we can design it, Brides by NoNA can take any outlandish idea for your wedding dress and make it into a spectacular reality. Nneka creates designs that are elaborate, elegant, unique and of high quality. And with our lavish tastes, it is hardly any wonder that the company has become a favorite among Nigerian brides.   With a little formal training in fashion design, Nneka is mostly a self-taught fashion designer but there is nothing amateur about her designs. An Investment Banker on Wall Street by profession, she started her bespoke formal wear business on a small scale designing dresses for only family and friends. However, the opportunity to expand her business came in 2013 when she designed the dresses for her twin sisters wedding and the wedding went viral on Instagram.   Since then, Brides by NoNA has been featured in high profile wedding publications such as MunaLuchi Bride, Duchess international magazine, Essence, BRIDES magazine and Modern Luxury Brides Atlanta. The company has also copped Wedding Wires Couples Choice Award for two consecutive years 2015 and 2016.   Of course, you could always purchase your dress on eBay or order one from Davids Bridal catalogue. But if you want your dress to fit you like a glove and make your guests wonder where on earth you bought it, then Brides by NoNA should be at the top of your list. Whats more is that the company offers packages with unlimited rounds of alterations so you can get your dress exactly how you want it.   So why buy a readymade dress when you can get one made to order? And in the words of Nneka, Its your day, your dress, so make it big, make it memorable and make it you. Contact Brides by NoNA to get your custom made bridal gown and bridesmaid dresses. Visit the website at:Brides at Nona

Our Naija wedding website connects African brides to experienced African wedding/events vendors, ranging from event planners, custom designers and caterers, to hair stylists, makeup artists, photographers, DJs, MCs, fabric consultants and more.

WHAT DOES LAMZOAKS MEAN?

LamzOaks is a fusion of two West African nicknames meaning my wealth has arrived and may Gods efforts not be in vain.

CAN WE SUBMIT A REAL WEDDING STORY TO YOUR BLOG?

Of course! Please send us an email with your story along with a high-resolution file photos. When submitting the photos, please send via drop box not via email.

WHAT IS LAMZOAKS?

LamzOaks is a vendor based website that focuses on connecting African and highly experienced American Vendors together for your African event based in the US. We are on a constant search for qualified and best in class vendors and because of this, we believe in quality over quantity.

We love vendor recommendations!! Email our team at info@lamzoaks.com along with their business name, website, and 3-4 sentences of why they should be considered. After your submission, our team will take it from here and begin to vet the recommended vendor.

IS THERE A MEMBERSHIP FEE TO BECOME A LAMZOAKS PREFERRED VENDOR?

Yes, we do obtain a membership fee. Email: info@lamzoaks.com to receive membership packages.

Choosing a Vendor Partner for LamzOaks is a something we take seriously, we review potential vendors portfolio, experience and their time in the industry. DO I HAVE TO BE AFRICAN TO BE A VENDOR?

No you dont have to be African to be a vendor, but we require you to have experience in African Weddings and events

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Privacy Policy

This privacy policy has been compiled to better serve those who are concerned with how their 'Personally Identifiable Information' (PII) is being used online. PII, as described in US privacy law and information security, is information that can be used on its own or with other information to identify, contact, or locate a single person, or to identify an individual in context. Please read our privacy policy carefully to get a clear understanding of how we collect, use, protect or otherwise handle your Personally Identifiable Information in accordance with our website. What personal information do we collect from the people that visit our blog, website or app? We do not collect personal information such as names, email address of credit card information from visitors of our site.   When do we collect information? We collect information from you when you or enter information on our site provide a vendor review. How do we use your information? We may use the information we collect from you when you surf the website, or use certain other site features to improve our website in order to better serve you.   How do we protect your information? We only provide articles and information. We never ask for credit card numbers therefore we do not use an SSL certificate, Malware Scanning , or any other vulnerability scanning and/or scanning to PCI standards. Do we use 'cookies'? Yes. Cookies are small files that a site or its service provider transfers to your computer's hard drive through your Web browser (if you allow) that enables the site's or service provider's systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information. They are used to help us understand your preferences based on previous or current site activity, which enables us to provide you with improved services. We also use cookies to help us compile aggregate data about site traffic and site interaction so that we can offer better site experiences and tools in the future. We use cookies to:
  • Understand and save user's preferences for future visits.
  • Keep track of advertisements.
  • Compile aggregate data about site traffic and site interactions in order to offer better site experiences and tools in the future. We may also use trusted third-party services that track this information on our behalf.
You can choose to have your computer warn you each time a cookie is being sent, or you can choose to turn off all cookies. You do this through your browser settings. Since browser is a little different, look at your browser's Help Menu to learn the correct way to modify your cookies. If you turn cookies off, some features will be disabled. It won't affect the user's experience that make your site experience more efficient and may not function properly. Third-party disclosure We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to outside parties your Personally Identifiable Information unless we provide users with advance notice. This does not include website hosting partners and other parties who assist us in operating our website, conduct our business, or serve our users, so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential. We may also release information when it's release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others' rights, property or safety. However, non-personally identifiable visitor information may be provided to other parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses. Third-party links We include or offer third-party products or services on our website. These third-party sites have separate and independent privacy policies. We therefore have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked sites. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome any feedback about these sites. Google Google's advertising requirements can be summed up by Google's Advertising Principles. They are put in place to provide a positive experience for users. https://support.google.com/adwordspolicy/answer/1316548?hl=en We have not enabled Google AdSense on our site but we may do so in the future. COPPA (Children Online Privacy Protection Act) When it comes to the collection of personal information from children under the age of 13 years old, the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) puts parents in control. The Federal Trade Commission, United States' consumer protection agency, enforces the COPPA Rule, which spells out what operators of websites and online services must do to protect children's privacy and safety online. We do not specifically market to children under the age of 13 years old. Fair Information Practices The Fair Information Practices Principles form the backbone of privacy law in the United States and the concepts they include have played a significant role in the development of data protection laws around the globe. Understanding the Fair Information Practice Principles and how they should be implemented is critical to comply with the various privacy laws that protect personal information. In order to be in line with Fair Information Practices should a data breach occur we will take responsive action and notify you via email within 7 business days. We also agree to the Individual Redress Principle which requires that individuals have the right to legally pursue enforceable rights against data collectors and processors who fail to adhere to the law. This principle requires not only that individuals have enforceable rights against data users, but also that individuals have recourse to courts or government agencies to investigate and/or prosecute non-compliance by data processors. Legal Disclaimer Though we make every effort to preserve your privacy we may need to disclose personal information when required by law wherein we have a good-faith belief that such action is necessary to comply with a current judicial proceeding, a court order or legal process served on our Web site. Notice of Changes We reserve the right to modify this privacy statement at any time, so please review it frequently. If we make material changes to this policy, we will notify you here, by email, or by means of a notice on our home page. If at some point in the future, there is a change to our information usage practices that affect your personally identifiable information, we will notify you by email of the relevant changes. At the time of this message, you will be able to opt-out of this information usage following the instructions in the email. We will also post the changes in our privacy statement 30 days prior to a change. You should also check this posted privacy statement for changes.   Last Edited on 2016-12-16 For email collection CAN SPAM Act The CAN-SPAM Act is a law that sets the rules for commercial email, establishes requirements for commercial messages, gives recipients the right to have emails stopped from being sent to them, and spells out tough penalties for violations. We collect your email address in order to:
  • Send information, respond to inquiries, and/or other requests or questions
  • Market to our mailing list or continue to send emails to our clients after the original transaction has occurred.
To be in accordance with CANSPAM, we agree to the following:
  • Not use false or misleading subjects or email addresses.
  • Identify the message as an advertisement in some reasonable way.
  • Include the physical address of our business or site headquarters.
  • Monitor third-party email marketing services for compliance, if one is used.
  • Honor opt-out/unsubscribe requests quickly.
  • Allow users to unsubscribe by using the link at the bottom of each email.
If at any time you would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, you can email us at
  • Follow the instructions at the bottom of each email.
and we will promptly remove you fromALLcorrespondence.   Contacting Us If there are any questions regarding this privacy policy, you may contact us using the information below. www.lamzoaks.com

item.title: The Art of Finesse Redefining Kids Birthday Parties in Dallas and Atlanta
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Magical kids birthday parties anyone? How about one made of dreams? When you need to pull out all the stops to make your little one feel really special on their birthday, The Art of Finesse has got your back. Based in Dallas, Texas and Atlanta Georgia, The Art of finesse is an event planning company that caters to kids parties and social events. Nike and Fisola own the company two sisters with a passion for delighting children with magical birthday parties and unforgettable memories. Whatever excites your child, be it dolls, cars, fairies, or princess, The Art of Finesse offers a range of packages with a difference. Packages include Pop Star Party, Enchanted Fairies, Princess Parties, Doll Parties and Tea with Duchess. Each party features themed party favors, group picture with celebrant and exciting themed activities. Nike and Fisola can transform any space into a beautiful birthday party setting. They even provide dessert tables and dessert carts. The sisters describe themselves as Party Stylists. They are expert planners and organizers bursting with creativity and armed with a desire to help materialize birthday wishes. Guided by their tagline, Fun Fresh Party Styling Nike and Fisola are passionate about what they do. Childrenare easier to please than adults but we never compromise on quality, said Nike. Plus, nothing is more rewarding than the gleeful smiles and delightful screams assuring us that we absolutely nailed it and made a birthday party wish come true. The Art of Finesse has built a solid reputation for being professional and consistent. Call them first when you need to stage a seamless, magical birthday for your little one. Prices start from $695 and the company caters for children 5 and up. Visit theirwebsiteto view their portfolio and to get ideas of what kind of party you would want for your child.

item.title: LamzOaks Vendors Blog Post
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: How LamzOaks Helped One Couple Pull of their Nigerian Wedding Launched only a few months ago, LamzOaks has already helped a number of couples to organize their African Wedding. In this post, we share with you how one couple, Temi and Osifo, used our vendor platform service to coordinate and pull off their spectacular Nigerian Wedding. Temi and Osifo live in New York but their wedding was hosted in Dallas Texas. The couple had a traditional Nigerian ceremony and a westernized wedding ceremony, plus a reception which highlighted their Nigerian culture. They catered for over 400 guests. The couple already had an idea of the services they wanted, so it really wasnt difficult to select the service providers that would help materialize their dream wedding. First on their list was Flawless Touch Makeover. This vendor offers make up and head tie services because no Nigerian bride is fully dressed until she has her head tie on. For the decor and floral arrangements, they used Flora Eventi- event design specialists for African weddings. As you can see from the photos, this vendor did a spectacular job with the decorations. They captured the theme of the wedding perfectly. Videography was provided by Inspired Effects. This vendor has a reputation for capturing beautiful timeless moments. And they did just that at Temi and Osifos wedding.   And the food? Oh, I had to leave that for last. Well, that was provided by Kemis Kitchen and Yemsade Catering. Together these caterers provided sumptuous, tantalising homemade African dishes that filled Temi and Osifos guests with waves of nostalgia. To top that off, FS Fruits & Arrangements provided an aesthetic display of a variety of fruits that were equally delicious. The arrangement looked so good, it seemed wrong to eat any of it. But it managed to serve its purpose to delight the eyes and the stomach. When we first launched LamzOaks, there were just a handful of vendors on the site. We had seventeen categories. In some categories, there was only one vendor- others had none. Today we have over 50 vendors and the number is expected to grow in the coming months. Like Temi and Osifo, if you harbor dreams of a flawless Nigerian wedding, then LamzOaks is the perfect place to start. Thanks to all our vendors for pulling off this gorgeous wedding! Decor-Prashe Decor Photography Olu Jr DJ-DJ Baggins Catering-Kemis Kitchen West African Cusine FS Fruits and Arrangements Videography-Inspired Effects

item.title: Shine Bright Like a Diamond with Touch of Jewel Events & Design
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Shine Bright Like a Diamondwith Touch of Jewel Events& Design You are obviously reading this post because you know that you dont have the skills or the time to dedicate to the planning of your special day. But weve got you covered. Touch of Jewel Event and Designs, LLC; popularly known as (TOJ) is another one of the impressive vendors on Lamzoaks that will assist in bringing your dream wedding to life. As specialists in event and wedding planning and designs, Touch of Jewel provides flawless execution of your wedding from start to finish. The company is owned by Jewel Odeyemi-a self confessed perfectionist with a very keen eye for detail.   How it Began TOJs story is an inspiring one. Jewel had been planning events as a hobby for friends and family, years before venturing into business. The extent of her skill was, however, tested in 2012 when she undertook the planning of her 400 guest wedding which was a success. Following the event, she started receiving requests from others to plan their wedding. By 2014 TOJ was established and she became a fully-fledged certified wedding and event planner.   The Affordability Factor Many brides prefer to take the risk of planning their own wedding because of the ridiculously high prices that some wedding planners charge. Jewel understands that fully well and that is why her services are very affordable. In fact, price quotes ranging from $1500 to $5,000 was the primary reason that forced her to plan her wedding. She said:I didnt have the luxury of paying such exorbitant amount to an event planner and I much preferred to put that money towards my dress, catering, florist or any other vendor I deemed more important. If you still cannot afford to spend that much on a wedding planner or if you happen to be a hands on bride and just need some planning advice, TOJ offers consultation services to clients who need that for a fee of $250 per hour to obtain as much information as you would like during that timeframe. If you are also looking for a La Carte services, they have packages starting out at $350.   Attention to Detail Touch of Jewel consults with you, discusses every request you have and develops a creative design for your wedding. They even attend all your vendor appointments, arrange your tastings and create a timeline for wedding party and guests, design the floor plan for your event and follow up with necessary vendors even after the event is over. They are with you from the moment you wake up in the morning as early as 5am up until the very last vendor has come to break down at your event, sometimes as late as 4am in the morning. I had the pleasure of using their services and believe me; it was like having my own personal assistant.   Opulence and Awesomeness Jewel is of Nigerian descent and, therefore, understands the lavish and opulent tastes of African brides. One of the most intriguing things about the company is that jewels are a major feature every event. This gives your guests the impression that you spent a fortune on your wedding even if you didnt.   The Reviews When you read the reviews on TOJs website, the one thing that keeps coming up is communication. And I can attest to that. With this company, you are not just another bride because Jewel and her team demonstrate real interest in you and what you want. Clients have referred to her as the backbone of their wedding ceremony, a life saver, top class and impeccable. Just recently, the company was featured in the prestigious Essence Magazine. And you know Essence only features the best.   Touch of Jewel offers a free one hour Skype, phone or face time consultation, so theres nothing stopping you from experiencing a hint of their stellar service. Why not contact them today? TOJ has made themselves easily available and they can be reached via any of the following mediums: Office Phone (972)244-3708 Mobile Phone (214)529-9204 Email Info@touchofjewel.com/touchofjewel@gmail.com Instagram @touch_of_jewel Facebook Touch of Jewel Events & Designs Twitter TOJ Events & Designs Snapchat Touchofjewel
